anyone have some great secrets for a spinach salad spinach salad this is a wonderful salad with a fabulous dressing ingredients cup diced red onion cup white sugar teaspoon ground black pepper teaspoon celery salt tablespoon mustard powder cup vegetable oil cup white wine vinegar eggs ounces fresh spinach chopped washed and dried head iceberg lettuce rinsed dried and chopped pound bacon cooked and crumbled cups crushed croutons red onion sliced in rings directions place eggs in a saucepan and cover completely with cold water bring water to a boil cover remove from heat and let eggs stand in hot water for to minutes remove from hot water cool peel and chop in a small saucepan combine the diced onion sugar black pepper celery salt mustard vegetable oil and vinegar whisk over high heat until all ingredients are well mixed and onions are translucent remove from heat and refrigerate until cool in a large bowl combine the eggs spinach iceberg bacon croutons and onion rings toss together pour dressing over salad and toss to coat evenly spinach salad with peaches and pecans ingredients cup pecans ripe peaches cups baby spinach rinsed and dried cup poppyseed salad dressing directions preheat oven to degrees f degrees c arrange pecans on a single layer on a baking sheet and roast in preheated oven for minutes until they just begin to darken remove from oven and set aside peel peaches if desired and slice into bite sized segments combine peaches spinach and pecans in a large bowl toss with dressing until evenly coated adding a little additional dressing if necessary spinach salad with baked goat cheese ingredients cups baby spinach rinsed and dried tablespoon butter clove garlic crushed cup plain bread crumbs ounces goat cheese sliced tablespoons balsamic vinegar tablespoons olive oil directions arrange the spinach on four plates in a skillet melt butter over medium heat and add crushed garlic cook and stir until slightly golden stir in breadcrumbs drop the goal cheese slices into the breadcrumbs a few at a time and turn to coat in the breadcrumb mixture place a slice or two of goat cheese on each serving of spinach and drizzle the salads with olive oil and balsamic vinegar wine tip try with a california sauvignon blanc Curry Gumbo Risotto McDonald's Brewery Domesticated turkey Cheese Sandwich Wok Idli Fish and chips Polish cuisine Chicken soup Pancake Ice cream Food preservation Dairy Roman eating and drinking Dumpling Sushi Chocolate French cuisine Ketchup Cookie Stir frying Cuisine of Singapore Wine Turkish coffee Cuisine of Malaysia Bearnaise sauce Gazpacho French toast Kosher foods Soy milk Cooking weights and measures Kraft Dinner Porridge Puff pastry Pasta Cuisine of Canada Japanese tea ceremony Buffalo wings Flax Martini cocktail Cincinnati chili Cake Cooking Cuisine of Argentina Sauerkraut Fish sauce Onion Pickling Meatball Casting 